CatDescriptText: Cutline from related article published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 22, 1967, pg. 13 reads: "The Georgian Room of the Hotel Webster Hall was the setting for the gala dinner-dance given by the Saide B. Hamilton Guild. The affair was in celebration of the Holy Cross Episcopal Church's 50th Anniversary."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of twenty-three women and Canon Junius Carter posed in ballroom of Hotel Webster Hall for Holy Cross Episcopal Church's 50th Anniversary Dinner Dance
